{"word":"ἀδύνατος","slug":"ἀδύνατος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>ἀδύνατος, ον</el></b> [<el>ἀ-</el><a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ priv.\">priv.</a>, <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:δύναμαι\">δύναμαι</a></el>] ‘lacking in capability’<b><p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>a.</pp></b> of <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ pers.\">pers.</a> <b><i>incapacitated, disabled</i></b> a lame man <b><a href='B:510 14:8'>Ac 14:8</a>;</b> in extended sense, as noun <el>οἱ ἀδύνατοι</el> <i>the weak</i> <b><a href='B:520 15:1'>Ro 15:1</a>.<p class=\"pp3\"/>—<pp>b.</pp></b> of things, <b><i>impossible</i> <a href='B:470 19:26'>Mt 19:26</a></b> and gospel parallels; <b><a href='B:520 8:3'>Ro 8:3</a>;</b> with <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ inf.\">inf.</a> <i>it is</i> <i>impossible</i> <b><a href='B:650 6:4'>Hb 6:4</a></b> <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ al.\">al.</a> in Hb. <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:ἀδυνατέω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:ᾄδω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}